"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:4.5.3\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">4.5.3</span> Robe</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מִדָּה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(midah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps133:2\">PSA 133:2</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מְעִיל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(m‘il)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:4\">EXO 28:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:31\">EXO 28:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:34\">EXO 28:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:5\">EXO 29:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:22\">EXO 39:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:23\">EXO 39:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:24\">EXO 39:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:25\">EXO 39:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:26\">EXO 39:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:7\">LEV 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:19\">1SA 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:27\">1SA 15:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:4\">1SA 18:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:5\">1SA 24:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:12\">1SA 24:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:12\">1SA 24:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:14\">1SA 28:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:18\">2SA 13:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:27\">1CH 15:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:3\">EZR 9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:5\">EZR 9:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:20\">JOB 1:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:12\">JOB 2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:14\">JOB 29:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:29\">PSA 109:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:17\">ISA 59:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:10\">ISA 61:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:16\">EZK 26:16</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ἔνδυμα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(enduma)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis18:24\">WIS 18:24</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ἱμάτιον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(himation)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:65\">MAT 26:65</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">περιστολή</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(peristolē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir45:7\">SIR 45:7</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ποδήρης</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(podērēs)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis18:24\">WIS 18:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir45:8\">SIR 45:8</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">στολή</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(stolē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir45:10\">SIR 45:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir50:11\">SIR 50:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc10:21\">1MA 10:21</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The robe of the High Priest was worn on top of the tunic and thus was a kind of jacket or overshirt. It was woven of light blue wool thread. It was a long garment, hanging down to the ankles. It is not clear whether it had sleeves or not, nor whether it was open or closed in the front. Somewhat like a Latin American poncho, it may even have been a rectangular piece of cloth with a hole in the middle for the head. Around the hem of the robe were sewn alternating golden bells (see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.5.3.1 Jinglet, bell&lt;REALIA:4.5.3.1&gt;</a>) and pomegranates made of woven threads. The robe was held in place by the ephod, which was worn over it. See the illustrations at <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.5 High Priest’s clothing&lt;REALIA:4.5&gt;</a> and <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.5.4 Ephod&lt;REALIA:4.5.4&gt;</a>.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>This garment is sometimes called “the robe of the ephod” (so <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:31\">EXO 28:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:5\">EXO 29:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:22\">EXO 39:22</a>). This means simply that the ephod was worn over it.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
